          {
            "@type": "@builder.io/sdk:Element",
            "@version": 2,
            "id": "builder-5ea05a5dd71a4e60b5cf1d4de708b77a",
            "component": {
              "name": "Copy",
              "options": {
                "rawHtml": "<p>Throughout the exhibition, blown-up prints of Weiler’s father's photographs are displayed on the walls, giving the appearance of flickering projections. Guests navigate through the dimly lit space using their flashlights while listening to audio stories. These stories include real voicemail messages between Weiler’s family members, conversations about illness, vulnerability and universal themes involving familial relationships.</p><p>\"You're moving through darkness using this flashlight to guide your way, and as you move, you're getting these fragments of stories, from heavy to light, but ultimately kind of universal — things that people have potentially experienced in relationships and families,” Weiler described. </p>"
              }
            },
